{"image_id": "KEY_2017_page_193", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Table of Contents", "bbox": [104.2, 22.7, 261.1, 43.7]}, {"text": "183", "bbox": [620.1, 1566.0, 654.9, 1589.3]}, {"text": "Capital Adequacy", "bbox": [104.2, 85.8, 278.2, 109.1]}, {"text": "KeyCorp and KeyBank (consolidated) must meet specific capital requirements imposed by federal banking", "bbox": [104.2, 135.8, 1089.5, 159.1]}, {"text": "regulators. Sanctions for failure to meet applicable capital requirements may include regulatory enforcement actions", "bbox": [104.2, 160.8, 1175.2, 184.1]}, {"text": "that restrict dividend payments, require the adoption of remedial measures to increase capital, terminate FDIC", "bbox": [104.2, 185.8, 1121.9, 209.1]}, {"text": "deposit insurance, and mandate the appointment of a conservator or receiver in severe cases. In addition, failure to", "bbox": [104.2, 210.8, 1170.7, 234.1]}, {"text": "maintain a “well capitalized” status affects how regulators evaluate applications for certain endeavors, including", "bbox": [104.2, 235.8, 1132.0, 259.1]}, {"text": "acquisitions, continuation and expansion of existing activities, and commencement of new activities, and could", "bbox": [104.2, 260.8, 1124.3, 284.1]}, {"text": "make clients and potential investors less confident. As of December 31, 2017, KeyCorp and KeyBank", "bbox": [104.2, 285.8, 1042.2, 309.1]}, {"text": "(consolidated) met all regulatory capital requirements.", "bbox": [104.2, 310.8, 599.7, 334.1]}, {"text": "KeyBank (consolidated) qualified for the “well capitalized” prompt corrective action capital category at", "bbox": [104.2, 360.8, 1040.9, 384.1]}, {"text": "December 31, 2017, because its capital and leverage ratios exceeded the prescribed threshold ratios for that", "bbox": [104.2, 385.8, 1111.6, 409.1]}, {"text": "capital category and it was not subject to any written agreement, order, or directive to meet and maintain a specific", "bbox": [104.2, 410.8, 1162.6, 434.1]}, {"text": "capital level for any capital measure. Since that date, we believe there has been no change in condition or event", "bbox": [104.2, 435.8, 1141.7, 459.1]}, {"text": "that has occurred that would cause the capital category for KeyBank (consolidated) to change.", "bbox": [104.2, 460.8, 972.7, 484.1]}, {"text": "BHCs are not assigned to any of the five prompt corrective action capital categories applicable to insured", "bbox": [104.2, 510.8, 1075.7, 534.1]}, {"text": "depository institutions. If, however, those categories applied to BHCs, we believe that KeyCorp would satisfy the", "bbox": [104.2, 535.8, 1140.5, 559.1]}, {"text": "criteria for a “well capitalized” institution at December 31, 2017, and since that date, we believe there has been no", "bbox": [104.2, 560.8, 1156.8, 584.1]}, {"text": "change in condition or event that has occurred that would cause such capital category to change.", "bbox": [104.2, 585.8, 998.2, 609.1]}, {"text": "Because the regulatory capital categories under the prompt corrective action regulations serve a limited supervisory", "bbox": [104.2, 635.8, 1174.0, 659.1]}, {"text": "function, investors should not use them as a representation of the overall financial condition or prospects of", "bbox": [104.2, 660.8, 1095.4, 684.1]}, {"text": "KeyBank or KeyCorp.", "bbox": [104.2, 685.8, 304.5, 709.1]}, {"text": "At December 31, 2017, Key and KeyBank (consolidated) had regulatory capital in excess of all current minimum", "bbox": [104.2, 735.8, 1140.5, 759.1]}, {"text": "risk-based capital (including all adjustments for market risk) and leverage ratio requirements as shown in the", "bbox": [104.2, 760.8, 1106.8, 784.1]}, {"text": "following table.", "bbox": [104.2, 785.8, 242.0, 809.1]}, {"text": "Actual", "bbox": [642.3, 852.9, 686.9, 869.2]}, {"text": "To Meet Minimum", "bbox": [807.7, 829.2, 929.8, 845.5]}, {"text": "Capital Adequacy", "bbox": [807.8, 843.8, 929.6, 860.1]}, {"text": "Requirements", "bbox": [820.1, 858.3, 917.3, 874.5]}, {"t